SIMPLE: greaten
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greaten
<hw>Great"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make great; to
aggrandize; to cause to increase in size; to expand.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A minister's [business] is to <qex>greaten</qex> and exalt [his
king].</q> <rj><qau>Ken.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greaten</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Greaten
<hw>Great"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become large; to
dilate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My blue eyes <qex>greatening</qex> in the looking-glass.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning. </qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>greatest</ent>⟦br⟧
